Dimon in talks to acquire Intabex Holdings . Dimon Inc said Tuesday it is in talks to acquire Intabex Holdings Worldwide SA , the world ' s fourth largest leaf tobacco dealer , with annual sales of about $ 700 million . Dimon said no definitive agreement had been reached . The company said in a release that its officials had no further comment . Dimon said it is the world ' s second largest leaf tobacco dealer and the largest exporter and importer of fresh - cut flowers . Dimon shares were off one early Tuesday afternoon at 22 - 1 / 4 . 
